  "text": "Bowel obstruction can be partial or complete. A complete obstruction is blockage in two locations of the bowel. On physical exam of an acute bowel obstruction, bowel sounds may be high-pitched and associated with pain. As the bowel becomes more distended, sounds will be muffled or absent. Percussion may initially be tympanic and resonant but may become duller as loops of bowel become dilated [CITATION_1] .",
